\subsection{Local--Global Recoverability Distinction}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\[
\boxed{
\text{reopenability}
\subset
\text{recoverability}
}
\]

Reopenability is local accessibility restoration.
Recoverability is global restoration of viable accessibility geometry.
A system may reopen locally while still failing to recover globally.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Interpretation}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

Recoverably differentiable admissible continuation defines the
primitive condition under which recursive organizational structure
may persist without catastrophic accessibility rupture.

Recursive emergence therefore does not arise from static
persistence alone,
but from the ability of recursive organizational trajectories to
remain:

\begin{itemize}
\item admissible,
\item navigable,
\item differentiably deformable,
\item locally reopenable,
\item globally recoverable,
\item and recursively continuable
\end{itemize}

under dissipative dynamics.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Dissipation Principle}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\[
\boxed{
\text{
Dissipation is not opposite emergence.
Stable emergence is constrained recoverable dissipation.
}
}
\]

Interpretation:

Recursive organizational systems do not persist by eliminating
dissipation,
but by preserving sufficiently recoverable admissible continuation
under ongoing deformation,
transport imbalance,
and energetic loss.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Recoverability Relation}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\[
\boxed{
\mathcal K_{\mathrm{DAC}}
\Rightarrow
\mathcal E_{\mathrm{rec}}.
}
\]

Interpretation:

Recoverability emerges whenever admissible continuation remains
sufficiently differentiable and reopenable to preserve recursive
future accessibility across recursive organizational geometry.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Cross-Layer Consequence}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

The same primitive recursive continuation kernel underlies:

\begin{itemize}
\item particle persistence,
\item chemical coordination,
\item biological regulation,
\item adaptive repair,
\item cognitive flexibility,
\item social adaptability,
\item and civilizational viability.
\end{itemize}

Each layer corresponds to stabilized recoverable continuation
across progressively richer recursive accessibility geometries.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Final Lock}
